==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brachiate
<hw>Brach"i*ate</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>brachiatus</ets> (<ets>bracch</ets>-) with boughs or branches like
arms, from <ets>brackium</ets> (<ets>bracch</ets>-) arm.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having branches in pairs, decussated, all nearly
horizontal, and each pair at right angles with the next, as in the maple
and lilac.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brachioganoid</ent>⟦br⟧
